1. System Preparation
Update the package repository and upgrade existing packages to ensure compatibility.

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install Apache2
Install the Apache web server package and verify that the service is running.

sudo apt install apache2 -y
sudo systemctl status apache2

3. Firewall Setup
Allow web traffic through the firewall using the pre-defined 'Apache' application profile.

sudo ufw allow 'Apache'
sudo ufw enable

4. Setting up the Web Root
Create a dedicated directory for your project files under /var/www/ and set the correct ownership and permissions for the ubuntu user.

sudo mkdir /var/www/your_domain
sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu /var/www/your_domain
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/your_domain

5. Website Content
Create a simple index.html file to test the configuration.

sudo vi /var/www/your_domain/index.html

<html>
    <head>
        <title>Welcome to Your_domain!</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Success! The your_domain virtual host is working!</h1>
    </body>
</html>

6. Virtual Host Configuration
Configure Apache to serve files from your specific directory by creating a new configuration file in sites-available.

sudo vi /etc/apache2/sites-available/your_domain.conf

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
    ServerName your_domain
    ServerAlias www.your_domain
    DocumentRoot /var/www/
    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/access.log combined
</VirtualHost>

7. Activating the Configuration
Enable the new site, disable the default Apache landing page, and restart the service.

sudo a2ensite your_domain.conf
sudo a2dissite 000-default.conf
sudo apache2ctl configtest
sudo systemctl restart apache2

Testing the Setup
To verify the installation, open your web browser and enter your server's public IP address:

http://your_server_public_ip

